Vice President Mike Pence gave a speech at the Michigan Farm Bureau, where he praised the Secretary of Agriculture, Sonny Perdue, and expressed gratitude to the farmers for their hard work and contributions to the American economy. He highlighted the administration's efforts in cutting taxes, reducing regulations, and negotiating fair trade deals, such as the USMCA, that benefit American farmers. Pence also criticized a presidential candidate's uninformed remarks about agriculture and emphasized the importance of farmers' character and faith in shaping the nation. He concluded by urging young people to consider careers in agriculture and assuring the audience that the administration will continue to support American farmers.